d how texts claimed to produce reliable and error-free modes of knowledge. The range of authors addressed-Leibniz, Adam Smith, Coleridge, Kant, and Goethe-demonstrates the diversity and heterogeneity underlying the textual production of the age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aError. 0aKnowledge, Theory ofzEuropexHistoryy18th century. 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 0aRhetoriczEuropexHistoryy18th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804775090zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804775090423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804775090.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles